cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about salient object detection using RGB-D images, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a two-streamed CNN architecture and a fusion module, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely sub-categories as well. Additionally, the paper involves optimization of a loss function, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses an end-to-end training approach, which involves neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category.
